<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!-- -->
<!-- Game options for new features in Better BTS AI -->
<!-- by jdog5000 -->
<!-- -->
<Civ4Defines xmlns="x-schema:CIV4GlobalDefinesSchema.xml">
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Use new air combat mechanics -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_AIR_COMBAT</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>1</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Allow AI to use Space victory strategy logic if space race victory is enabled -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_VICTORY_STRATEGY_SPACE</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>1</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Allow AI to use Conquest victory strategy logic if conquest victory is enabled  -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_VICTORY_STRATEGY_CONQUEST</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>1</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Allow AI to use Domination victory strategy logic if domination victory is enabled  -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_VICTORY_STRATEGY_DOMINATION</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>1</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Allow AI to use Culture victory strategy logic if culture victory is enabled  -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_VICTORY_STRATEGY_CULTURE</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>1</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Allow AI to use Diplomacy victory strategy logic if diplomacy victory is enabled  -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_VICTORY_STRATEGY_DIPLOMACY</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>1</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
	<!-- Better BTS AI: Vassals of human player build some extra
	     military units (recommended for multiplayer only)
		 kekm.3: 'Taken care of by K-mod's "prepare for war"
		 vassal option, so unnecessary?' -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_HUMAN_VASSAL_WAR_BUILD</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>0</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Changes behavior of defensive pacts (Def: 0) :
			0 : Default BTS
			1 : Defensive pacts do not cancel when a player has war declared on them
			2 : Turns defensive pacts into alliances, so they are now also offensive pacts.  Plus pacts
				do not cancel when war is declared.  Does not change name/description in game.
			kekm.3: Set to 1 and 'can be signed while at war' (if 1 or 2;
			though 2 is bugged)
		 -->
		<!-- custom: not sure what this is about exactly but anyways etc, cancelling defensive pacts if war is declared on them seems to make sense though, whatever peace or not happens after war if any would need to be redefined, does not seem to make much sense unless i am mistaken that a player A at war with player B can convince/compell player B at all to attack player C while player A is still at war with player B. The default BTS behavior, if i understood it correctly, seems to make much more sense unless i'm mistaken anyways etc. But just like a peace treaty being enforced unbreakably, it is maybe also nice to have some kidn of rules that make agreements be enforced, but in the case of defensive pacts, it seems a bit too far fetched, and maybe could be abused by human players to manipulate AIs, or affect AI vs AI negatively to the profit of the human player as well (or maybe also AI affecting the human player negatively to a quite forced defensive pact, but if such were the case the game would probably be lost even though not sure, still it is an inconvenience as well), so make these based on trust rather if i may say rather than hard enforced obligatory obligation if i may say but anyways etc. As for the opposite possibility of farming defensive pacts then cancelling them (like giving defensive pact vs defensive pact + X where W is any thing in a trade anyways etc) by declaring war would be too tedious and not worth the hassle or not enjoyable, i have not tried it myself so i don't know, so just mentioning this hypothetical possibility anyways etc. In short, if i am not mistaken, restore default BTS behavior of defensive pacts between players being broken when a player has declared war on the other if i understood it correctly and am not mistaken in my understanding anyways etc, was 1 -->
		<DefineName>BBAI_DEFENSIVE_PACT_BEHAVIOR</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>0</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
	<Define>
		<!-- Better BTS AI: Allows human player to offer themselves as vassal to an AI.  The AI has been taught to value this appropriately.  (Def: 0) 
		advc.112: The BBAI default was 0; 1 in K-Mod. Not supported in AdvCiv.
		-->
		<DefineName>BBAI_HUMAN_AS_VASSAL_OPTION</DefineName>
		<iDefineIntVal>0</iDefineIntVal>
	</Define>
</Civ4Defines>
